\par Dancing Lights
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Light]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 0, Sor/Wiz 0
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effect:}{\fs20\cf0  Up to four lights, all within a 10- ft.-radius area
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 minute (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par Depending on the version selected, you create up to four lights that resemble lanterns or torches (and cast that amount of light), or up to four glowing spheres of light (which look like will-o\rquote 
-wisps), or one faintly glowing, vaguely humanoid shape. The }{\i\fs20\cf0 dancing lights }{\fs20\cf0 must stay within a 10-foot-radius area in 
relation to each other but otherwise move as you desire (no concentration required): forward or back, up or down, straight or turning corners, or the like. The lights can move up to 100 feet per round. A light winks out if the distance between you and it 
exceeds the spell\rquote s range.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Dancing lights }{\fs20\cf0 can be made permanent with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency }{\fs20\cf0 spell.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Darkness
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Darkness]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 2, Clr 2, Sor/Wiz 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, M/DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Object touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par This spell causes an object to radiate shadowy illumination out to a 20-foot radius. All creatures in the area gain concealment (20% miss chance). Even creatures that can normally see in such conditions (su
ch as with darkvision or low-light vision) have the miss chance in an area shrouded in magical }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par Normal lights (torches, candles, lanterns, and so forth) are incapable of brightening the area, as are light spells of lower level. Higher level light spells are not affected by }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness.
\par }{\fs20\cf0 If }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness }{\fs20\cf0 is cast on a small object that is then placed inside or under a lightproof covering, the spell\rquote s effect is blocked until the covering is removed.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Darkness }{\fs20\cf0 counters or dispels any light spell of equal or lower spell level.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Arcane Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A bit of bat fur and either a drop of pitch or a piece of coal.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Darkvision
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Rgr 3, Sor/Wiz 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par The subject gains the ability to see 60 feet even in total darkness. Darkvision is black and white only but otherwise like normal sight. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Darkvision }{\fs20\cf0 does not grant one the ability to see in magical darkness.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Darkvision }{\fs20\cf0 can be made permanent with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency }{\fs20\cf0 spell.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 Either a pinch of dried carrot or an agate.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Daylight
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Light]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 3, Clr 3, Drd 3, Pal 3, Sor/Wiz 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Object touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par The object touched sheds light as bright as full daylight in a 60-foot radius, and dim light for an additiona
l 60 feet beyond that. Creatures that take penalties in bright light also take them while within the radius of this magical light. Despite its name, this spell is not the equivalent of daylight for the purposes of creatures that are damaged or destroyed b
y bright light.
\par If }{\i\fs20\cf0 daylight }{\fs20\cf0 is cast on a small object that is then placed inside or under a light- proof covering, the spell\rquote s effects are blocked until the covering is removed.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Daylight }{\fs20\cf0 brought into an area of magical darkness (or vice versa) is temporarily negated, so that the otherwise prevailing light conditions exist in the overlapping areas of effect.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Daylight }{\fs20\cf0 counters or dispels any darkness spell of equal or lower level, such as }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness.
