\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This enchantment clouds the mind of a humanoid creature with 4 or fewer Hit Dice so that it takes no actions. Humanoids of 5 or more HD are not affected. A dazed subject is not stunned, so attackers get no special advantage against it.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A pinch of wool or similar substance.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Daze Monster
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 2, Sor/Wiz 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target: }{\fs20\cf0 One living creature of 6 HD or less
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 daze, }{\fs20\cf0 but }{\i\fs20\cf0 daze monster }{\fs20\cf0 can affect any one living creature of any type. Creatures of 7 or more HD are not affected.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Death Knell
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Death, Evil]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 2, Death 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Living creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous/10 minutes per HD of subject; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par You draw forth the ebbing life force of a creature and use it to fuel your own power. Upon casting this spell, you touch a living creature that has \endash 1 or
 fewer hit points. If the subject fails its saving throw, it dies, and you gain 1d8 temporary hit points and a +2 bonus to Strength. Additionally, your effective caster level goes up by +1, improving spell effects dependent on caster level. (This increase
 in effective caster level does not grant you access to more spells.) These effects last for 10 minutes per HD of the subject creature.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Death Ward
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 4, Death 4, Drd 5, Pal 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Living creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par The subject is immune to all death spells, magical death effects, energy drain, and any negative energy effects.
\par This spell doesn\rquote t remove negative levels that the subject has already gained, nor does it affect the saving throw necessary 24 hours after gaining a negative level.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Death ward }{\fs20\cf0 does not protect against other sorts of attacks even if those attacks might be lethal.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Deathwatch
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Evil]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  30 ft.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Cone-shaped emanation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par Using the foul sight granted by the powers of unlife, you can determine the condition of creatures near death within the spell\rquote 
s range. You instantly know whether each creature within the area is dead, fragile (alive and wounded, with 3 or fewer hit points left), fighting off death (alive with 4 or more hit points), undead, or neither alive nor dead (such as a construct).
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Deathwatch }{\fs20\cf0 sees through any spell or ability that allows creatures to feign death.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Deep Slumber
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 sleep, }{\fs20\cf0 except that it affects 10 HD of creatures.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Deeper Darkness
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Darkness]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  One day/level (D)
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness}{\fs20\cf0 , except that the object radiates shadowy illumination in a 60-foot radius and the }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness }{\fs20\cf0 lasts longer.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Daylight }{\fs20\cf0 brought into an area of }{\i\fs20\cf0 deeper darkness }{\fs20\cf0 (or vice versa) is temporarily negated, so that the otherwise prevailing light conditions exist in the overlapping areas of effect.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Deeper darkness }{\fs20\cf0 counters and dispels any light spell of equal or lower level, including }{\i\fs20\cf0 daylight }{\fs20\cf0 and }{\i\fs20\cf0 light.
\par }{\fs20\cf0 
\par }{\cf0 Delay Poison
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Healing)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 2, Clr 2, Drd 2, Pal 2, Rgr 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Fortitude negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par The subject becomes temporarily immune to poison. Any poison in its system or any poison to which it is exposed during the spell\rquote s duration does not affect the subject until the spell\rquote s duration has expired. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Delay poison }{
\fs20\cf0 does not cure any damage that poison may have already done.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Delayed Blast Fireball
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Fire]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  5 rounds or less; see text
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 fireball, }{\fs20\cf0 except that it is more powerful and can detonate up to 5 rounds after the spell is cast. The burst of flame deals 1d6 points of fire damage per caster level (maximum 20d6).
\par The glowing bead created by }{\i\fs20\cf0 delayed blast fireball }{\fs20\cf0 can detonate immediately if you 
desire, or you can choose to delay the burst for as many as 5 rounds. You select the amount of delay upon completing the spell, and that time cannot change once it has been set unless someone touches the bead (see below). If you choose a delay, the glowin
g
 bead sits at its destination until it detonates. A creature can pick up and hurl the bead as a thrown weapon (range increment 10 feet). If a creature handles and moves the bead within 1 round of its detonation, there is a 25% chance that the bead detonat
es while being handled.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Demand
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 8
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will partial
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 sending, }{\fs20\cf0 but the message can also contain a }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 (see the }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 spell), which th
e subject does its best to carry out. A successful Will save negates the }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 effect but not the contact itself. The }{\i\fs20\cf0 demand, }{\fs20\cf0 if received, is understood even if the subject\rquote 
s Intelligence score is as low as 1. If the message is impossible or meaningless according to the circumstances that exist for the subject at the time the }{\i\fs20\cf0 demand }{\fs20\cf0 is issued, the message is understood but the }{\i\fs20\cf0 
suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 is ineffective.
\par The }{\i\fs20\cf0 demand}{\fs20\cf0 \rquote s message to the creature must be twenty-five words or less, including the }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion. }{\fs20\cf0 The creature can also give a short reply immediately.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A short piece of copper wire and some small part of the subject\emdash a hair, a bit of nail, or the like.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Desecrate
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Evil]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 2, Evil 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  20-ft.-radius emanation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  2 hours/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell imbues an area with negative energy. Each Charisma check made to turn undead within this area takes a \endash 3 profane penalty, and every undead creature entering a }{\i\fs20\cf0 desecrated }{\fs20\cf0 
area gains a +1 profane bonus on attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws. An undead creature created within or summoned into such an area gains +1 hit points per HD.
\par If the }{\i\fs20\cf0 desecrated }{\fs20\cf0 area contains an altar, shrine, or other permanent fixture dedicated to your deity or aligned higher power, the modifiers given above are doubled (\endash 
6 profane penalty on turning checks, +2 profane bonus and +2 hit points per HD for undead in the area).
\par Furthermore, anyone who casts }{\i\fs20\cf0 animate dead }{\fs20\cf0 within this area may create as many as double the normal amount of undead (that is, 4 HD per caster level rather than 2 HD per caster level).
\par If the area contains an altar, shrine, or other permanent fixture of a deity, pantheon, or higher power other than your patron, the }{\i\fs20\cf0 desecrate }{\fs20\cf0 
spell instead curses the area, cutting off its connection with the associated deity or power. This secondary function, if used, does not also grant the bonuses and penalties relating to undead, as given above.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Desecrate }{\fs20\cf0 counters and dispels }{\i\fs20\cf0 consecrate}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A vial of unholy water and 25 gp worth (5 pounds) of silver dust, all of which must be sprinkled around the area.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Destruction
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Death]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 7, Death 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Fortitude partial
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell instantly slays the subject and consumes its remains (but not its equipment and possessions) utterly. If the target\rquote 
